<p>See part 4. Phlebas the Phoenician and Mr. Eugenides,
        the Smyrna merchant - both of whom appear later in the
        poem - are different phases of the same symbolic
        character, here identified as the "Phoenician
        Sailor." Mr. Eugenides exports "currants"
        (line 210). The drowned Phlebas floats in the
        "current" (line 315).</p>
